This is dhrystone, compiled according to the spec:
 1. Files dhry_1.c and dhry2_.c compiled separately.
 2. No inlining.
 to run in demo TB:

  make -f $RV_ROOT/tools/Makefile [<simulator>] TEST=dhry

The iteration count defaults to 1000. Override it with DHRY_RUNS for a longer
run (runtime scales ~linearly), e.g. ~1800 s on a typical event simulator:

  make -f $RV_ROOT/tools/Makefile [<simulator>] TEST=dhry DHRY_RUNS=27000

A prebuilt long version (27000 runs) is committed as testbench/hex/dhry_long.hex
and runs via the canned-hex flow when no RISC-V toolchain is installed:

  make -f $RV_ROOT/tools/Makefile [<simulator>] TEST=dhry_long

